reviews.headline: I would buy this product again and again
reviews.comments: This product is great and it's not the first time I've used it. When I was a student I used to live around the corner from Kiehls in the East Village, NYC but thought they were to expensive to shop there. Now I guess spending a little extra is not so scary.

reviews.headline: Did not work for me
reviews.comments:
Kiehl's would not let me post this review on their website, so it just goes to show you how they filter out the negative reviews.

I received a travel size in one of those birch box things and used it every now and then and loved how it lathered and felt after washing my face so I decided to get a larger bottle when I eventually ran out. I started using this everyday and it destroyed my face. I started getting red bumps on my cheek, my acne hadn't been that bad since high school. I ended up throwing it in the trash. Once I started using Cerave products my skin cleared up in a week or so. This stuff is so expensive compared to your typical skincare brands and didn't work well for me at all, very disappointed.

reviews.headline: The need to have!
reviews.comments: So this is a face wash for men, but it is great for anyone. It is refreshing and does not have a strong fragrant smell. It is easy on my skin and really makes my skin feel amazing. It keeps my skin clear, not that I'm very acne prone, and happy! I use it morning and night and I don't know if I could ever switch.

reviews.headline: Boyfriend Loves It!
reviews.comments: Got a sample for my boyfriend a while ago and he really isn't into skin care but I convinced him to give it a try bc he gets acne every now and again. he loved it and I ended up getting the full size for his birthday this year. It's perfect for his skin which is oily/combination and helps prevent acne and even skin tone!

reviews.headline: Great for son's acne
reviews.comments: I buy this for my son, it works great at keeping his face clean and clear. He has moderate/bad acne and this works perfect!

reviews.headline: For men but I use it anyway
reviews.comments: If you like your face to feel moisturized after you wash it you might not like this.  I love the way I feel cleaned afterwards but it's a dry clean.  It does have a nice fragrance of mint but I love a lot of fragrance.

reviews.headline: Best
reviews.comments: I'm female and this is the BEST face wash- have used it for years and has kept my face clear! Once my wife started using it too, it was a helpful factor in clearing up her acne. Cannot live without and not just for men!!

reviews.headline: I will buy it again.
reviews.comments: Great product, worked well for teenage facial.

faceoff_positive.comments: I have used this product since it came out a few years ago. It lathers readily such that a bottle lasts a VERY long time. The scent is bracing, but light. My skin feels thoroughly clean, but never dried out. I realize it has caffeine as an ingredient. Not sure if caffeine really does anything if applied topically, but I pretend that it does anyway. The only downside is the bottle. The cap on this and other similar Kiehl's products is not good for travel. (I gave up after 3 of these on other Kiehl's products leaked in my toiletries bag during a flight.) Wonderful product, but if you fly..watch out. You will be rinsing your bag in the hotel bathtub.
faceoff_positive.headline: One of the best men's face cleansers one can find

faceoff_negative.comments:
This is a great product for cleaning your skin without drying it out, but it is not versatile enough to be your only cleanser. Whenever I have some dry or rough skin on my face -- especially in the winter -- I find that this face wash just cleans the surface and does not improve the texture of my skin at all. Even though this face wash doesn't claim to be an exfoliant, it is nonetheless frustrating to have to use another product or a cloth to take off dry skin and restore even texture. I'm not fussy about my skin, but I do like it to be in good shape.

Another down side is that it sometimes dries out your skin, even though the label states that it works "without an over-drying effect". If you use this face wash and then shave, expect to use a fair bit of moisturizer to keep dryness away.

On the plus side it smells great, produces great lather, rinses off easily, and leaves your skin feeling fresh and clean. I use it at the end of my shower before shaving, and it helps soften hair and prepare the skin for a comfortable shave.

Overall a good product, but not as excellent as the other Kiehl's stuff I use (Facial Fuel, Facial Fuel SPF 15, Lite Flite Shave Cream).
faceoff_negative.headline: Not versatile enough to be your only cleanser
